    "description": {
      "value": "<p><b>Source</b> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 43</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 137</em></p>\n<h3><span class=\"pfs-conditional\" title=\"No character may purchase a firearm unless she possesses the Gunsmithing feat and firearms are never considered Always Available\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3>\n<p><b>Cost</b> 1,600 gp <b>Weight</b> 6 lbs.</p>\n<p><b>Damage</b> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <b>Critical</b> x4; <b>Range</b> 30 ft.; <b>Type</b> B and P; <b>Special</b> -</p>\n<p><b>Misfire</b> 1-2 (5 ft.); <b>Capacity</b> 1</p>\n<p><b>Category</b> Two-Handed; <b>Proficiency</b> Exotic</p>\n<h3>Description</h3>\n<p>This short musket features an axe blade at the end of its barrel. It can be used as both a musket and a battleaxe. It is considered a double weapon for the purposes of creating masterwork or magical versions of this weapon.</p>\n<p>If this firearm gains the broken condition, both the firearm component and the axe are considered broken. An axe musket uses either a bullet and a single dose of black powder or an alchemical cartridge as ammunition.</p>\n<p><b>This is an early firearm.</b></p>"
